To target mobile devices like smartphones, you can use media queries in your CSS. Media queries allow you to apply different styles based on the characteristics of the device, such as screen size, resolution, and orientation.

Here's an example of a media query that targets devices with a screen width of 480 pixels or less:

```css
@media only screen and (max-width: 480px) {
  /* Styles for mobile devices */
  body {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
}
```

In this example, the font size of the body element is set to 16 pixels for devices with a screen width of 480 pixels or less. You can adjust the media query to target different screen sizes or other device characteristics as needed.

